      "difficulty": "medium",
      "questionText": "Simplify $\\dfrac{3x^2 - 12}{x^2 - x - 6}$.",
      "answerType": "expression",
      "correctAnswer": "$\\dfrac{3(x - 2)}{x - 3}$",
      "tolerance": null,
      "unit": null,
      "markScheme": [
        { "mark": "M1", "desc": "Numerator factorised: $3(x-2)(x+2)$" },
        { "mark": "M1", "desc": "Denominator factorised: $(x-3)(x+2)$" },
        { "mark": "A1", "desc": "$\\dfrac{3(x-2)}{x-3}$ cao" }
      ],
      "workingSteps": [
        "Numerator: $3x^2-12 = 3(x^2-4) = 3(x-2)(x+2)$",
        "Denominator: $x^2-x-6$; need product $-6$, sum $-1$: $-3$ and $+2$",
        "$x^2-x-6 = (x-3)(x+2)$",
        "$\\dfrac{3(x-2)(x+2)}{(x-3)(x+2)} = \\dfrac{3(x-2)}{x-3}$",
        "Verify $x=4$: $\\frac{3(16)-12}{16-4-6}=\\frac{36}{6}=6$; result: $\\frac{3(2)}{1}=6$ ✓"
      ],
      "explanation": "Factorise numerator and denominator fully, then cancel the common factor $(x+2)$."
    },
